Package: dck
Version: 1.10.0
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: iproute2, iptables, util-linux, procps, curl, ca-certificates
Recommends: ufw, git
Maintainer: animesao <animesao@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: dck — lightweight container runtime
 No daemon. No Docker. Just containers.
 .
 dck is a ~5 MB static binary that runs OCI/Docker containers
 using Linux namespaces (PID, Mount, Net, UTS, IPC), overlayfs,
 cgroups v2, and bridge networking. No dockerd needed.
 .
 Features:
  * Pull and run OCI images from Docker Hub
  * Bridge networking with port mapping (iptables DNAT)
  * Resource limits (memory, CPU via cgroups v2)
  * Volume mounts, environment variables, healthchecks
  * Restart policies (always, on-failure, unless-stopped)
  * Multi-container config via dck.toml
  * Interactive exec, attach, logs
  * dck stats — live resource monitoring
Homepage: https://github.com/animesao/dck
